cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper discusses benchmarking and analyzing Open Information Extraction (OIE) systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques and evaluation metrics, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The use of data sets from the news domain and Wikipedia suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper's focus on improving OIE systems and identifying research directions aligns with the scope of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
